url = {https://doi.org/10.1145/3730436.3730527},
abstract = {Under the development of sensing technology, human behavior recognition based on sensor signals is now a key technology in intelligent health monitoring, smart home and human-computer interaction. Especially the real time accurate recognition of human behavior sequence has great practical significance in improving user experience and intelligence of the system in these applications. Meanwhile, traditional human behavior recognition methods always suffer some problems, such as noise interference, unstable signal and insufficient ability of features extraction, thus it is particularly important to improve the accuracy and robustness of the recognition algorithm. In this paper, we propose an end-to-end deep learning model named VMDFormer, which is built through the introduction of Variational Mode Decomposition (VMD) and Channel Self-Attention Mechanism (SE-Attention) to a deep neural network. Specifically, the model combines VMD with Random Forest algorithm and introduces the mechanism of SE-Attention for feature representation. Through VMD decomposition to extract multi-scale feature from the data, the key feature in VMD decomposition are used by the Random Forest algorithm. Besides, the feature representation is deepened by introducing Channel Attention. In the experiments, we design the proposed method and compare with the baseline method. The results show that the proposed approach can obtain excellent performance with classification rate of 98.65 \%. This work can provide the efficient and robust method for human behavior recognition, and the synergistic combination of Channel Attention mechanism and the multi-scale signal decomposition will also be a useful guide in Intelligent Health Monitoring and Human computer Interaction field.},
